<p><font size="12" color="#000000">Having worked at Runtime Revolution for less than three months I was somewhat daunted when asked to write an article for the company newsletter. My main problem was coming up with a suitable topic. As a result I looked to my colleagues for inspiration and was supplied with some rather creative suggestions. Given the Edinburgh office's current obsession with the board game Scrabble however, and the fact that the Technology team are performing rather poorly in the current office competition, I quickly settled on a 'Revolution Word Finder' in a bid to improve our performance (but not cheat - of course!).</font></p>